cardwithimageandlink.title: TAPP and Ride
cardwithimageandlink.text:
PATH has launched TAPP, or Total Access PATH Payment, a new contactless fare payment system. With TAPP you can pay for your ride directly at the turnstile with a contactless credit/debit card or smart device.

TAPP is now available at all stations. As the pilot continues, the system will gradually expand to additional turnstiles.

TAPP turnstiles do not accept SmartLink or MetroCard. Please continue to use non-TAPP turnstiles when paying with these fare media. TAPP does not accept OMNY.

imagewithtext_copy_c_1138602833.subtitle: Weekends through January 2026
imagewithtext_copy_c_1138602833.text:
Due to critical rail replacement and track stabilization work in the vicinity of multiple PATH stations, Journal Square-bound trains on the 33 St. - JSQ (via HOB) line will include an additional stop at Exchange Place Station every weekend through January 2026.

PATH will continue to operate every 20 minutes on the NWK-WTC and JSQ-33 (via HOB) lines, and run temporary, additional service between Hoboken and 33 Street stations.

9 St. & 23 St. stations are closed daily from 11:59 PM 5 AM for station maintenance. Please use Christopher St., 14 St., or 33 St. Station.

imagewithtext_copy_c.subtitle: Weekend Service Changes
imagewithtext_copy_c.text:
NWK-WTC Service Change
7:20 AM - 4 PM Saturday

PATH is replacing 6,000 feet of track between Journal Square and Harrison stations. This work will reduce the impact of delays on passengers and is expected to be completed in 2024.

Due to this track work, there will be adjusted service on the NWK-WTC line. 

All NWK- and WTC-bound trains will stop at Journal Square for up to 10 minutes before departure. Additionally, trains will be operating at  slower speeds.

We apologize for the inconvenience.

imagewithtext_copy_1.title: Get Customized PATH Alerts Pushed to Your Lock Screen
imagewithtext_copy_1.text:
Download the RidePATH app to receive push service alerts that are customized to your route and time of day.

With the RidePATH app, you will also be able to:

  • View real-time train departures at each PATH station
  • Learn about weekend service changes that may impact your trip
  • Look up train schedules by station even when underground
  • Set your favorite stations so your normal commute schedule is easily accessible

Download For iOS here >

Download For Android here >
